  <span id="freeText13532350812156461761" style="display:none">In this book Kate Thayer has been living a pretty good life. She is a veterinarian, and runs the family horse farm. The farm is where is always feels at home more than anywhere else. BUT, there is one place in the house she has never been allowed to go....the attic. What is up there? She is an adult now, why can't she go up there? After sneaking the key to the attic from her grandmother, Kate, never knew how much her world was going to be torn to pieces. Can Kate forgive and forget? Will she be able to make herself "whole" again by finding someone she never knew existed? You will need to read the book to find out. I received a copy of this book from the author. The review is entirely my own opinions and done voluntarily.</span>
