        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2090741471?book_show_action=true">Aug 12, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Molly" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Molly" href="/user/show/68264176-molly">Molly</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/30082617-shattered-lies">review of another edition</a>

          <div><span class="uitext greyText">Recommends it for: </span>
           <span class="uitext reviewText">Fans of southern literature, 60s vs today</span></div>

          <div>
    <span class="greyText">Recommended to Molly by: </span>
      Axpauthors.com, arc copy, voluntary review
  </div>


    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2090741471" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer8904394745481241459">A southern veterinarian discovers many family mysteries when going through a few dusty boxes. <br/><br/>Heartbreaking father&apos;s suicide and mothers death in childbirth turn out to be tied to racial tensions. <br/><br/>She uncovers a sibling she never knew about, and family connections that are truly blood, rather than just affection. <br/><br/>Sadly, grandparents who crossed racial lines in friendship in the 60s give in to bigotry in their children&apos;s and grand children&apos;s relationships. <br/><br/>A sudden health scare brings all the sur</span>
  <span id="freeText8904394745481241459" style="display:none">A southern veterinarian discovers many family mysteries when going through a few dusty boxes. <br /><br />Heartbreaking father's suicide and mothers death in childbirth turn out to be tied to racial tensions. <br /><br />She uncovers a sibling she never knew about, and family connections that are truly blood, rather than just affection. <br /><br />Sadly, grandparents who crossed racial lines in friendship in the 60s give in to bigotry in their children's and grand children's relationships. <br /><br />A sudden health scare brings all the surviving members of the family together to face love and loss, and to try to work through guilt and hopes for their futures as individuals and families. <br /><br />The personal, emotional details are well painted to really bring out that some prejudices had more to do with broken hearts, trust and friendships, than to do with understandings and perceptions of black and white. <br /><br />I received an arc copy, and volunteered my review. This moving story is one I'd gladly read at any price. </span>
  <a data-text-id="8904394745481241459" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


