<div id="review_2172537206" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2172537206" />
    <a title="Carla" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/6140682-carla"><img alt="Carla" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/f_50x66-6a03a5c12233c941481992b82eea8d23.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2172537206?book_show_action=true">Nov 02, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Carla" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Carla" href="/user/show/6140682-carla">Carla</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/30082617-shattered-lies">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2172537206" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer17054989851232058844">This book hooked me from the first chapter. To imagine that racial tension between whites and blacks marring in the 1980&apos;s really surprised me. The way both families treated the son and daughter who wanted to marry and then the the twin children later is appalling. Maybe it is because it happened in the south it was more frowned upon. The author used brutal honesty in portraying the characters in this novel. It read like it could have happened yesterday with the racial divide we are experiencing</span>
  <span id="freeText17054989851232058844" style="display:none">This book hooked me from the first chapter. To imagine that racial tension between whites and blacks marring in the 1980's really surprised me. The way both families treated the son and daughter who wanted to marry and then the the twin children later is appalling. Maybe it is because it happened in the south it was more frowned upon. The author used brutal honesty in portraying the characters in this novel. It read like it could have happened yesterday with the racial divide we are experiencing these days. Kuddos to the author for bringing such a sensitive subject up. Can't wait to see what the author writes next. Definitely a winner here.</span>
  <a data-text-id="17054989851232058844" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
